<%= error_messages_for(@user) %>

<title>Welcome to our wonderful domain!</title>
<meta name="description" content="A desciption of our website and introduction.">
<%= stylesheet_link_tag('application') %>
<%= render(:partial => "default")%>

<p>Current Date is: <%= Time.now.month%>-<%= Time.now.day%>-<%= Time.now.year%></p>
<p>Current Time is: <%= sprintf("%02d",Time.now.hour%12)%>:
  <%= sprintf("%02d",Time.now.min)%>
  <%if Time.now.hour/12 >= 1%>
    <%= "pm"%>
  <%else%>
    <%= "am"%>
  <%end%>

<p>The sky-maps require that you utilize IE9+ or Chrome to be able to view and
interact with the SVG properly. <strong>You must also be logged into the app to access them.</strong></p>

<p><em>For all maps it is assumed to be 9pm-12pm, which is the ideal time to view most (visible) constellations.
  The blue circle indicates a possible field-of-view</em></p>

<h2><%= link_to("Current", {:action => 'current'})%></h2>

<article>The "Current" map is designed to allow a user to interact with a sky-map
that is representative of the current month. One is also able to "shift" the map
by choosing a different month and will be given a different set of constellations to
work with.</article>

<h2><%= link_to("West", {:action => 'west'})%></h2>
<article>The "West" map is a sky-map over Vancouver, BC, more accurately during the month of February.
  It is preset and much easier to follow than "Current."</article>

<h2><%= link_to("East", {:action => 'east'})%></h2>
<article>The "East" map is a sky-map over Moscow, Russia, more accurately during the month of February.
  It is preset and much easier to follow than "Current". One may notice that
it is very similar to the Vancouver map.</article>

<h2><%= link_to("Zodiac", {:action => 'zod'})%></h2>
<article>"Zodiac" is a map which spans the whole year and is used to identify
the twelve signs of the zodiac. It is the easiest map to complete as there are little
to no interfering constellations and stars.</article>

<div class="star_container"></div>
</div>
